product.product_name: Addlink S20 120GB 2.5" SATA III 6Gb/s 3D Nand SSD
Addlink S20 120GB 2.5" SATA III 6Gb/s 3D Nand SSD
product.description:
• Addlink S20 120GB 2.5" SATA III 6Gb/s 3D Nand SSD

    Addlink S20 SSD comes with 120GB 2.5" SATA III 6Gb/s capacity and built in with 3D NAND flash technology. The Addlink S20 achieves exceptional transfer speeds of up to 510MB/s read and 400MB/s write. Easy upgrade for speeding up computer performance. This Addlink SSD has built-in SmartECC and SmartRefresh for state of the art data retention and ensures continued reliable data transfer.

    Exceptional Performance

    This Addlink S20 SSD gives you Exceptional Performance with the taking full advantage of the SATA III 6Gb/s interface and built in with 3D NAND flash, and also the S20 SSD achieves exceptional transfer speeds of up to 510MB/s read and 400MB/s write.

    S20 SATA III 6Gb/s:

    Addlink S20 SSD comes with the latest 3D NAND technology that features vertical expansion of storage cells. By using only high-quality flash chips and enhanced firmware algorithms, the S20 SSD is guaranteed to provide greater performance and reliability.

    The latest 3D NAND Technology

    This Addlink SSD featured with 3D NAND technology. The 3D NAND flash is a type of flash memory, where the memory cells are stacked vertically in multiple layers. This 3D NAND is developed to break through density limitations of the 2D planar NAND, that deliver a greater level of performance and endurance.

    The latest Addlink S20 120GB 2.5" SATA III 6Gb/s 3D Nand SSDcomes with 03 years warranty.

product.product_name: Anti Virus Software care protection for mac 2022
Anti Virus Software care protection for mac 2022
product.description: The Apple M1 chip with built-in Secure Enclave brings the same powerful security capabilities of iPhone to Mac — protecting your login password, automatically encrypting your data, and powering file-level encryption so you stay safe. And the Apple M1 chip keeps macOS secure while it’s running, just as iOS has protected iPhone for years.
product.specification: The best way to keep your Mac secure is to run the latest software. When new updates are available, macOS sends you a notification — or you can opt in to have updates installed automatically when your Mac is not in use. macOS checks for new updates every day and starts applying them in the background, so it’s easier and faster than ever to always have the latest and safest version.
